message: "If you use Kappa-FIN or the Kappa Method observables (Ξ, Oh, φ, η) in your research, please cite as below."
type: software
title: "Kappa-FIN: Topological Early Warning System for Financial Market Crises"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-03-01"
license: CC-BY-4.0
url: "https://github.com/odavidohio/kappa-fin"
repository-code: "https://github.com/odavidohio/kappa-fin"

authors:
  - family-names: "Ohio"
    given-names: "David"
    email: "odavidohio@gmail.com"
    orcid: ""

abstract: >
  Kappa-FIN applies the Kappa Method — persistent homology H₁ of rolling
  correlation networks combined with Forman-Ricci curvature — to detect
  systemic risk precursors in financial markets. The system uses two
  complementary criteria (Rayleigh: Ohio Number Oh; Prandtl: damage integral
  φ) with automated CALM baseline identification (including the KCPT
  knee-phi-tail anti-contamination penalty) and dual crossing detection.
  Validated across seven historical crisis scenarios including the 2008
  Global Financial Crisis, COVID-19 crash, dot-com bubble, 1987 crash,
  Volmageddon 2018, Euro/Taper tantrum, and the 2022 Fed rate hike cycle.

keywords:
  - topological data analysis
  - persistent homology
  - financial markets
  - systemic risk
  - early warning signals
  - Forman-Ricci curvature
  - correlation networks
  - Kappa Method
  - Law of Ohio
  - 2008 financial crisis
  - COVID-19 market crash

